items.name: Super Pose Book Vol.1 - ControlNet
items.description:
Super Pose Book Vol.1

for use with ControlNet

BACKGROUND:

  • This is a pack of 30 poses curated to help you make a pose magazine

  • These poses are made for use with ControlNet and have been tested SFW and NSFW

USAGE RECOMMENDATION:

txt2img Setup:

  • Aspect Ratio 3:2 OR 1152 (h) x 768 (w)

  • Sampling steps 20-50

  • CFG Scale 5-12

  • Sampling Method: Euler A (others work too)

ControlNet Setup:

  • Download ZIP file to computer and extract to a folder

  • Inside you will find the pose file and sample images

  • Inside the automatic1111 webui, enable ControlNet

  • Load pose file into ControlNet, make sure to set preprocessor to "none" and model to "control_sd15_openpose"

  • Weight: 1 | Guidance Strength: 1

  • Click big orange "Generate" button = PROFIT! :)

==========================================

Note: Using different aspect ratios can make the body proportions warped or cropped off screen. This is normal, to avoid this issue make sure the aspect ratio of the txt2img and ControlNet pose image are the same.

ControlNet here: https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet

ControlNet pretrained models: https://huggingface.co/lllyasviel/ControlNet/tree/main/models

OR smaller file version of same models prepared by theally: https://civitai.com/models/9251/controlnet-pre-trained-models

Put the ControlNet models (.pt, .pth, .ckpt or .safetensors) inside the models/ControlNet folder

==========================================

Please leave me a review or post images of your creations.

If I get good feedback, I will release more volumes. Enjoy!

Check out my channel for other great models: https://civitai.com/user/tokyoidolsafk

The girl in the samples: https://civitai.com/models/13006/gem-gloria-tang-gem

items.name: Shigure Kosaka - HSDK
items.description:
A Nice Waifu from Shijou Saikyou no Deshi Kennichi.

Works fine with: <lora:KousakaShigureV2:0.7>, kousaka_shigure, ponytail,

I was only able to isolate one outfit:

  • ShigurePinkOutfit (It her typical pink kimono with an under mesh top)

This was supposed to be an easy retrain but instead i had to clean up the dataset. My oldest loras are really showing their age, I am surprised how nice they came out in retrospect.

I have also added the dataset and the tags summary file so people can experiment.

Note stroked though text are for V1

Might be a bit of a failure. I was only able to get her zigzagged eyebrows at high weight .65+and high steps 30+

She looks perfectly fine at .4 weight but she will be missing her characteristic eyebrows.

Got more accurate results with: <lora:Kousaka_Shigure:.65>, Kousaka_Shigure, big_breasts, eyebrows_visible_through_hair

Got better and consistent results but normal eyebrows result with: <lora:Kousaka_Shigure:.45>, Kousaka_Shigure, big_breasts,

Note: eyebrows_visible_through_hair is not a trigger but without it images are less likely to show the zigzag pattern in her eyebrows.

items.name: Bluethebone esthetic (80s style)
items.description:
Bluethebone Anime aesthetic 80s (✿ ͡❛ ᴗ ͡❛)

New version Bluethebone 2.0R, 2.1R, 2.2R (full remake) on Patreon

I made a video on how to achieve the same quality or just repeat my art

just use hires fix as much as your video card is capable of, so as not to give an error, with 8gb of video memory it is 512x768 with hires fix 2, upscaler Latent (nearest-exact) or just Latent (if there are problems with the image), the picture will be much more detailed.

LORA weight from 0.2 to 1 depending on your goals, 1 - closer to the original style, there are no restrictions here

CFG Scale - 3.5-6

Eta noise seed delta 31337

Use Abyssorangemix3aom3_aom3a3.safetensors With these negative prompts:
(worst quality, low quality, extra digits:1.4), text, title, logo, patreon logo, patreon username, copyright name, signature, artist name, watermark, deformed, subtitled, web address
(too many text in arts)


Spent more than 25 hours removing 99% of the text and logs that were in almost every art, so there is no need for negative prompts associated with the text, which will increase the quality, but still can occur. In versions 2.0R, 2.1R, 2.2R there is practically no text in the art.


Trigger Words: 1980s \(style\), bluethebone

Combined with my other LORA

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

    *Information taken from Lykon

    Please post your work with or without comments, it will help me improve. Thanks!

    If you like my work, click on the heart above, I will be pleased :3

items.name: 【Character】Widowmaker (Overwatch) 3-in-1
items.description:
2023/3/1 update

Reduce loss to 0.09. 0.6 and 0.7 weight should be enough. The usage is unchanged.

Introduction

A LORA model of Widowmaker from Overwatch, including 3 outfits: default, black lily and cote d'azur. The 784MB VAEs are recommended. 0.6~0.8 weights are good.

Usage

Firstly, I set three corresponding tags for these three outfits. So do not use the booru tag widowmaker \(overwatch\).

  • For default outfit, the trigger tag is widow-normal. The key features are: ponytail, head-mounted display, bodysuit, purple skin.

  • For black lily outfit, the trigger tag is widow-lily. The key features are: china dress, chinese clothes, purple skin, hair bun, flower, hair flower. You can also add 'head-mounted display'. It's optional.

  • For cote d'azur outfit, the trigger tag is widow-cotedazur. The key features are: blue bikini, beach, eyewear on head, purple skin, front-tie bikini top, hair pulled back, short sleeves, sunglasses.

See the preview images for details. Btw, the preview images are generated using EasyNegative embedding.

items.name: D.Va (Overwatch) LORA
items.description:
My fifth Overwatch LORA. Mainly focused on original appearance + a bit of Academia skin.

  • Original - prompt is d.va , I chose not to burn in her hair fully so you more easily could change hairstyles (for example ponytail), trigger for authentic one is simply long hair.

  • Academia - d.va, alternate hairstyle, twin braids, blazer, bespectacled, glasses, school uniform, pleated skirt

Checked strength range is 0.6-0.8.

Slight issue is headphones - there's barely any images, let alone good ones with D.Va without her headphones. As result - it's rather hard to get rid of them with original skin, and just a bit easier with Academia.

Triggers for paticular things are:

  • Outfit - bodysuit, headphones, pilot suit, ribbed bodysuit, shoulder pads, turtleneck, thigh boots, thighhighs

  • Accesories - bunny print (rabbit logo, easy to inpaint to fix one on bodysuit, or to add it on other things), clothes writing, headphones, bubblegum, finger gun

If you liked my work, you can donate here.

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.

Trained on Anything V4.5 with anime.vae.pt.

Samples are 512x768, without HighRes.fix (mostly), using OrangeCocoa 50/50 Mix , with OrangeMix VAE, and using EasyNegative embedding, CLIP Skip 2. Inpaint examples are txt2img with 1 single inpaint done on face (I will comment on exceptions).

items.name: The Redheaded Libertarian
items.description:
This TI attempts to capture the likeness of "The Redheaded Libertarian" on Twitter. TRHL is an artist, model, and political commentator recognized for her intelligence, sharp wit, eponymous red hair, pronounced cheekbones, green eyes (central heterochromia) and seemingly age-defying youthful appearance.

Used with the SD1.5 base model, it will create a reasonable likeness of the source. Used with any other model, it will add "TRHL" features, typically pronounced cheekbones and a demure look.

The TI was using A1111 with 3400 steps.

Please note! Only the base SD1.5 model seems to capture the likeness. If you're using a different model, you may want to inpaint using the base SD1.5 model if reproducing the general likeness is important.

For whatever reason, using the base SD1.5 model, this TI wants to make the persona older by adding excessive crow's feet around the eyes. You'll need to negative prompt wrinkles, old, elderly, etc. to get the image closer to real life. If using another model (e.g. Deliberate) you can remove these negative prompts, as the TI will typically produce a younger female.

Please note, most of these images have had some level of inpainting or face restoration. The base prompts will get you 90% of the way there, but you'll need to work a bit to get better hair, add freckles, etc.

The initial images are a combination of SD1.5 base for the likeness with Deliberate for the details. The last few images were rendered with different models, and you can see what a huge difference that produces in the output. The models used are noted in the prompt details.

Prompts are formatted for Invoke. If you're using A1111, you'll need to modify accordingly.

modelVersions.description: Trained using SD1.5 with A1111. 3400 steps. This TI was trained on images from the TRHL Twitter feed, mainly selfies. It lends itself to these same sorts of images. You'll get the most realistic results using the base SD1.5 model for the face. I used Deliberate to inpaint and get better hair and face restoration to get the eyes to pop.

items.description:
Viper (Valorant) Character LoRA

If you enjoy my models and want to support me you could buy me a coffee!

This LoRA mimics the character Viper from Valorant.

WARNING: This LoRA is very strong! I recommend anywhere from 0.5-0.75 weight depending on what you want in your image.

The example images were created with NeverEndingDream on varying weights but feel free to experiment on your own. I tried briefly to mix it with a couple of different embeddings and it gave back decent results but you might find a better way to mix them (changing different weights etc.).

items.name: Fairy Knight Tristan/Baobahn Sith (FGO)
items.description:
Fae Knight Tristan from Fate Grand Order. There is a normal TI somewhere out there, but no LORA yet, so here you go. It includes all 3 of her ascensions plus a "freefit" mode for help with alternate costumes.

Be careful with the tags and tokens. There are a bunch, with two calling upon literally every image in the dataset (baosith and fktristan, testing suggests that you don't use them), 3 for each ascension (1asc, 2ndasc, 3rdasc), and 2 more for custom outfits (freefit and alternate costume). The asc tokens were meant to simply be used by themselves so they would generate the corresponding outfit without any specifics, but each time I trained this LORA that plan failed. So they more or less just guide the ai to what needs generating. Same with the freefit token, though it should have more effect on the second LORA. I should also stress that like the first two tokens, DO NOT USE HER DANBOORU TAG. I am uncertain if it really makes a difference, but it seems all three of those tags just confuse the AI and fuck up the clothes.

Tags aside, every outfit seems to come out pretty accurate for the most part. That said, below you'll find two LORAs to download, because strangely, while one of them failed mostly to grasp the clothing concept, it simultaneously generates REALLY neat images compared to the other. So if you want my advice, use that one specifically for alternate outfits, and the main one for Sith's ascensions.

Additionally, regarding the main LORA, I also advise you to exclude any unused outfit tokens in the negatives prompt, because sometimes just one tag (like grey skin) might cause it to jumble up the clothes and give you some kind of amalgamation.

Lastly, don't ever expect it to get the heels right. It never will.

TLDR:

  • Don't use baosith, fktristan, OR HER TAG NAME. Just prompt the outfit tags and details (see previews).

  • Use the Freefit LORA to help with custom outfits, and the final version for her canonical ones.

  • It will always fuck up the heels, there ain't no way it's gonna be consistent with that.

  • When trying for one ascension outfit, make sure to exclude the tokens for the others in the negative pompt.

  • Beware of tags that apply to all her outfits, specifically grey skin or pale skin. Head specific tags should be fine.

  • Her first outfit sometimes gives her the headpiece from 2nd asc, just put "black headpiece" in the negs to fix that.

  • You'll notice this soon enough, but perhaps thanks to either me or all the artists that have drawn Sith, she will have her hand by her mouth in an ojousama-ish pose 85% of the time, unless prompted to do otherwise.

Trained on NAI with 202 images (Freefit with 162), extensively tested across multiple models. NSFW capable and mostly style compatible (mainly in freefit mode).

Images in preview may be from past versions! Do not expect full replication!

items.name: Maria Guardiola (Instagram celeb)
items.description:
Maria Guardiola, daughter of legendary football manager Pep Guardiola, is a model and social media influencer with about 500K followers on Instagram.

For her TI, I have used 25 images taken from her Instagram account and other sites. This time I've slightly modified my usual method: I've only used 4 tokens, 2500 steps, a different gradual learning rate (0.05:10, 0.02:20, 0.01:60, 0.005:200, 0.002:500, 0.001:1500, 0.0005), and kept the usual batch size (3) and gradient accumulation (2). The result is, finally, no apparent overtraining, and as far as I can tell a pretty flexible TI that should adapt well to your favorite prompts. Hope you like it!

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
About time this TI had a new version, I think. It was one of my first embeddings and, even though I still like the results it produces, I feel like perhaps Maria's facial features were a bit exaggerated and sometimes could seem a bit cartoonish.

I've retrained the TI from scratch after eliminating a few pics. The final dataset consisted on 20 images. I trained until step 1000 at a 0.004 learning rate, as usual, and then until 1850 steps with a 0.002 learning rate. I've tested the model and gotta say it's just where I wanted it to be, so for now I won't be training it any more. Hope you all like it!

items.name: Spider Man: Into the Spider-Verse LoRA
items.description:
Creating these models takes time, money, and effort and it's great when that effort is rewarded. If you really like it you can buy me a coffee ☕.

If you like this model please consider checking out some of my other projects. I've made LoRAs to emulate the style of Super Crooks, Fullmetal Alchemist, Death Note, and Chainsaw Man.

This is Just a LORA that emulates the style of the movie Spider Man: Into the Spider-Verse. Depending on the subject you're trying to create, you'll need to play around with the strength. All these images were created with Dreamshaper and Deliberate as the models. X-formers is on.

I've found this model is a lot less fire and forget than my others. It may be because of the unique animation style. I may train a checkpoint later down the road and see if it's better. As you can see from the examples it is quite good.

One known issue: It seems to really have problems with people of color sometimes. Other times it generates them with no problems. It may be because it's overtrained on Miles' face, but they often end up looking like him to one degree or another. If I decide to retrain this model I will likely prune the dataset significantly. It is possible to fiddle with the settings and get a good PoC, but it's harder than it probably should be. Frankly though, this is an issue with all AI models to one extent or another and something everyone in the AI community should be thoughtful about.

I trained it on around 4,000 still images from the movie, so it's quite good at emulating the style. No need to give it a particularly lengthy prompt these images were generated with really simple prompts.

This LORA mixes well with others as well. So if you want a trained character/person in the Spider Man: Into the Spider-Verse style that's possible. If you have any questions, comments, or concerns feel free to send me a message. I'm happy to chat about my methodology.

Going forward I'm going to upload the training data for all my models. Gathering these images in this quantity isn't something everyone in the community can do, so providing them will give model makers stronger tools.
